&lt;p&gt;When I first scaled the &lt;a href="https://redis.io/topics/cluster-spec"&gt;Redis cluster&lt;/a&gt;, I was very worried because I thought it was a difficult task.
But luckyly &lt;a href="https://redis.io/"&gt;Redis team&lt;/a&gt; has done a nice work. They provides the &lt;code&gt;redis-trib&lt;/code&gt; tool to help us with some cluster tasks.
This tutorial requires you have a working redis cluster. You also need &lt;a href="https://www.ruby-lang.org/en/"&gt;Ruby&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href="https://rubygems.org/gems/redis/versions/4.0.3"&gt;Redis gem&lt;/a&gt; to be install. Remember to choose the compatible version of Redis gem with your Redis version.
Let's check the status of my cluster with this command below.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;redis-trib.rb info &lt;span class="m"&gt;10&lt;/span&gt;.20.0.1:6379
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


